cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.ME 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with inertial parameters identification for a humanoid robot. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new parametrization and optimization problem to solve the inertial identification problem. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the iCub humanoid robot used in the experiments has cameras for visual perception. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper deals with physical consistency of inertial parameters which is important in control systems. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with physical properties of rigid bodies.
